# Windsurf cold-start entry (K-HARDEN-8 cross-CLI alignment)

This project uses a cross-agent harness. Windsurf follows the same canonical
contract as Claude Code, Codex CLI, Gemini CLI, Aider, and Cursor.

## Read order
1. AGENTS.md (canonical shared agent contract)
2. HARNESS_PLAYBOOK.md (operating manual)
3. skills/SUBAGENT_HARNESS.md (subagent template)
4. constitution.md (axioms)

## Hard rules (enforced by hooks)
- PR-only: never `git push origin main`. Always feature branch + PR.
  Server-side GitHub branch protection blocks direct push universally.
- No wildcard staging: never `git add .` / `-A` / `--all`. Explicit paths only.
- No sidecar: never stage handover/evidence/dev_self_hosting/dev_*/
- Restricted surfaces (AGENTS.md §6) need per-atom architect §8.

## Coding style
- skills/KARPATHY_ARCHITECT.md — first-principles, monolithic-flat
- skills/KARPATHY_SIMPLE_CODE.md — transparent data flow, no Manager/Factory/Engine

## Setup once per clone
- bash scripts/install_hooks.sh
- bash scripts/setup_branch_protection.sh

AGENTS.md is canonical. Conflicts → AGENTS.md wins.
